{title: Zap-Cannon}
- Zap-Cannon is a devastating Electric-type move known for its high voltage and paralyzing effect; it unleashes a massive blast of electricity with pinpoint accuracy, though its power comes at the cost of lower accuracy under normal circumstances
- Zap-Cannon is frequently employed by advanced Electric-type Pokemon and specialized trainers due to its ability to incapacitate foes; the sheer force of the attack often leaves targets paralyzed, rendering them vulnerable to follow-up strikes

{title: Power-Whip}
- Power-Whip is a devastating Grass-type move where the user lashes out with thick, vine-like appendages to strike the opponent with brutal force; it is often employed by Pokemon like Tangrowth or Mega Venusaur, whose natural physiology enhances its destructive potential
- Power-Whip carries immense kinetic energy, capable of shattering barriers or sending foes crashing through terrain; trainers favor it for its raw power, though its accuracy can be unreliable in the heat of battle

{title: Lets-Snuggle-Forever}
- Lets-Snuggle-Forever is Mimikyu's exclusive Z-Move, a devastating Fairy-type attack that channels the Pokemon's desperate longing for affection into overwhelming force; beneath its ragged disguise, Mimikyu unleashes this move with a surge of spectral energy, striking opponents with the full weight of its loneliness
- Lets-Snuggle-Forever manifests as a haunting embrace, trapping foes in an inescapable hold before delivering a crushing blow; the move's power reflects Mimikyu's tragic backstory, amplifying its strength when fueled by the desire to be loved
